{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_2","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' .claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md\"","aggregated_output":"# ACTIVE_PLAN\n\nTrack Status: active\n\n## Milestone Status\n\n- [x] Milestone 1 — Architecture Stabilization\n- [x] Milestone 2 — Board Interaction Quality\n- [x] Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer\n- [x] Milestone 4 — Operational Reliability\n- [x] Milestone 5 — Publishable Product Quality\n\n## Current Task Plan\n\n- `task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md`\n\n## Current Slice\n\n- [ ] Task 6 slice — add one shared host-side live-thread resolver before mailbox actions write `.codex-team` task or agent state.\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n- Run the mailbox track on a 1 minute loop unless the user explicitly overrides it.\n- Treat 1 minute as the canonical cadence; earlier 10 minute and 2 minute mailbox notes are historical drift, not the current source of truth.\n- Keep the audit result fixed: Task 4 is now effectively closed in code, the no-team-space dashboard path plus the missing-loop-daemon render path are already verified, and mailbox write paths are already isolated from legacy thread-status mutations.\n- Keep the planning result fixed: no further plan-shaping analysis is needed before the next bounded execution slice.\n- Keep the review-window result fixed: the newest two mailbox analysis loops, including the legacy-status isolation closure, found no new regression or drift beyond the already-scoped resolver slice.\n- Keep the review-window bookkeeping fixed: the current two-loop analysis requirement is refreshed and satisfied for this mailbox handoff state.\n- Keep the analysis discipline result fixed: the mailbox track now has an established two-loop review pattern recorded in task-plan and loloop notes, so the remaining Task 6 gap is execution hardening rather than review-process setup.\n- Keep the rule-level review result fixed: the mailbox task plan now reflects that the two-loop review rule is already established process, not an open planning gap.\n- Keep the audit freeze fixed: further analysis passes should not change the resolver execution target unless a new regression or containment need appears.\n- Keep the resolver spec fixed: no further analysis narrowing is needed beyond `panel.lastPayload.dashboard.threads` unless a real regression or containment need appears.\n- Keep the remaining-gap result fixed: with no containment trigger in the current review window, the only unresolved Task 6 work is the live-thread resolver pair plus the syntax-check step that follows the future code change.\n- Keep the next pass hardening-first: execute the remaining Task 6 stale-thread validation work in `task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md` by adding one shared live-thread resolver in `src/host/team-coordination.js`, sourcing it from `panel.lastPayload.dashboard.threads`, and using it only in `assignTaskToThread`, `claimTaskForThread`, `heartbeatThread`, `blockTaskForThread`, and `completeTaskForThread`.\n- Keep the execution boundary fixed: do not expand that slice into mailbox UI changes, stale-lease recovery, or broader supervisor flow changes.\n- Keep the closure rule fixed: the resolver slice should close both Task 6 thread-validation checkboxes together, because the resolver is the concrete implementation of the stale-thread rejection outcome.\n- If the hardening pass finds risk to current stable behavior, pause feature expansion and route the following pass to containment or rollback-friendly isolation.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
